SELECT m.id, 'HMI Interface Programming/Overview', 'hmi-interface-programming', '<h2>HMI Interface Programming/Overview</h2><h3>Purpose</h3><p>This procedure explains how to safely update the Human Machine Interface (HMI) software using a USB drive and verify proper communication with the PLC after the upgrade.</p><hr><h3>Required Materials</h3><p>Before beginning, ensure you have:</p><ul><li>HMI update package (.zip file)</li><li>USB flash drive</li><li>USB-A to Micro-USB adapter</li><li>Access to the HMI panel</li><li>System configuration password (if required)</li></ul><hr><h3>Safety &amp; Preparation</h3><p>Before starting:</p><ul><li>Verify the correct update package has been provided.</li><li>Confirm the update ZIP file is copied to the USB drive.</li><li>Ensure power remains connected throughout the update process.</li><li>Do not remove power or disconnect the USB drive during the upgrade.</li></ul><hr><h3>HMI Upgrade Procedure</h3><h3>Step 1: Prepare the USB Drive</h3><ol><li>Copy the HMI update package ZIP file onto a USB flash drive.</li><li>Safely eject the USB drive from your computer.</li></ol><p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> USB drive contains the update package and is ready for installation.</p><h3>Step 2: Connect the USB Drive</h3><ol><li>Connect the USB flash drive to the USB-A to Micro-USB adapter.</li><li>Insert the adapter into the HMI USB port located on the back of the display.</li><li>Touch and hold the HMI screen for approximately <strong>3–5 seconds</strong>.</li></ol><p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> The System Menu appears on the display.</p><h3>Step 3: Start the Update</h3><ol><li>From the System Menu, select: <strong>Update</strong></li><li>When the update screen appears, select: <strong>NEXT</strong></li><li>Allow the HMI to process the update.</li></ol><p><strong>Expected Result:</strong></p><ul><li>Update files are verified.</li><li>Installation begins automatically.</li><li>Multiple update screens may appear.</li><li>Progress bars may be displayed during the installation process.</li><li>Do not remove the USB drive during this step.</li></ul><h3>Step 4: Wait for Automatic Reboot</h3><p>After the update completes:</p><ol><li>The HMI will automatically reboot.</li><li>Once rebooting is complete, remove the USB drive.</li></ol><p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> The HMI starts normally and is ready to communicate with the PLC.</p><hr><h3>Post-Upgrade Verification</h3><h3>Verify PLC Communication</h3><p>After startup:</p><ol><li>Observe the HMI for normal operation.</li><li>Confirm process values and status indicators appear correctly.</li></ol><p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> The HMI and PLC automatically synchronize and operate normally.</p><hr><h3>Troubleshooting</h3><h3>Communication Warning Messages</h3><p><strong>Symptoms</strong></p><ul><li>Warning icons displayed</li><li>PLC communication alarms</li><li>Missing process data</li></ul><p><strong>Corrective Action</strong></p><ol><li>Turn off power to the control panel.</li><li>Wait approximately 10 seconds.</li><li>Restore power.</li></ol><p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> PLC and HMI communication re-establishes successfully.</p><h3>Temperature Readings Incorrect</h3><p><strong>Symptoms</strong></p><ul><li>Temperature displays showing 32°F</li><li>Unrealistic process temperatures</li><li>Sensor values appear incorrect</li></ul><p><strong>Corrective Action</strong></p><ol><li>Enter the system configuration menu.</li><li>Enter the authorized password.</li><li>Verify all configuration settings are correct.</li><li>Confirm the <strong>Configuration Flag</strong> at the end of the configuration sequence is enabled/set.</li></ol><p><strong>Expected Result:</strong> Temperature readings return to normal operating values.</p><hr><h3>Upgrade Checklist</h3><ul><li>Update ZIP copied to USB drive</li><li>USB connected to HMI</li><li>System Menu accessed</li><li>Update selected</li><li>NEXT button pressed</li><li>Update completed successfully</li><li>HMI rebooted</li><li>USB removed</li><li>PLC communication verified</li><li>Temperature readings verified</li></ul><h3>Success Criteria</h3><p>The upgrade is considered successful when:</p><ul><li>HMI boots normally</li><li>PLC communication is established</li><li>No warning indicators are present</li><li>Process values display correctly</li><li>Temperature readings are accurate</li></ul><p><strong>Procedure Complete</strong></p>', 41, TRUE, 7
